human gut metagenome; Patient 2 Day 1; P2-D1
disease: bowel symptoms: presence of defecatory urgency; 3 stools (2 in form of diarrhea)
samp_collect_device: Feces were self-collected by the volunteers in tubes containing 10 mL of phosphate buffered saline (PBS). Samples were kept at 4 ºC until their storage at -80 ºC (approximately 2 hours after being collected)
samp_mat_process: Before nucleic acid extraction, fecal samples were resuspended in PBS and centrifuged at 4,000 rpm for 3 min to remove fecal debris. 1-4 mL of the supernatants were centrifuged at 14,000 rpm for 3 min to recover cell pellets

Description - Title: human gut metagenome; Patient 2 Day 3.1; P2-D3.1
disease: bowel symptoms: presence of abdominal pain, abdominal distension and defecatory urgency; 11 stools (11 in form of diarrhea)
samp_collect_device: Feces were self-collected by the volunteers in tubes containing 10 mL of phosphate buffered saline (PBS). Samples were kept at 4 ºC until their storage at -80 ºC (approximately 2 hours after being collected)
samp_mat_process: Before nucleic acid extraction, fecal samples were resuspended in PBS and centrifuged at 4,000 rpm for 3 min to remove fecal debris. 1-4 mL of the supernatants were centrifuged at 14,000 rpm for 3 min to recover cell pellets

Description - Title: human gut metagenome; Patient 2 Day 3.2; P2-D3.2
disease: bowel symptoms: presence of abdominal pain, abdominal distension and defecatory urgency; 11 stools (11 in form of diarrhea)
samp_collect_device: Feces were self-collected by the volunteers in tubes containing 10 mL of phosphate buffered saline (PBS). Samples were kept at 4 ºC until their storage at -80 ºC (approximately 2 hours after being collected)
samp_mat_process: Before nucleic acid extraction, fecal samples were resuspended in PBS and centrifuged at 4,000 rpm for 3 min to remove fecal debris. 1-4 mL of the supernatants were centrifuged at 14,000 rpm for 3 min to recover cell pellets
